Indication in the context of respiratory conditions. 
 Hedera helix is indicated for some symptoms of respiratory disease, namely expectorant (a medicine that helps to bring up phlegm) for productive (chesty) coughs (
 EMA, 2015a). Other related indications include its actions as antispasmodic and in the treatment of flu and fever (
 Bisset, 1994; 
 Blumenthal et al., 1998; 
 Hong et al., 2015; 
 Kruttschnitt et al., 2019).
